  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released\u00a010/30/2017 1:43 PM CT (18:43 UTC)</p><h2 id=\"id-1.13.9-Qpop\u2122Updates\">Qpop\u2122 Updates</h2><p>We have been working hard to\u00a0make Qpop easier to setup and maintain, and this update contains improvements in several areas.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.13.9-ImprovedConnectionHandling\">Improved Connection Handling</h3><p>We\u00a0have improved the handling of connects/disconnects\u00a0so that you can maintain a\u00a0more stable connection between your point of sale terminal and your Qpop companion.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.13.9-Companionresets\">Companion resets</h3><p>If you need to pair an already running companion, now you can\u00a0reset a Qpop companion with a long press/click-and-hold interaction\u00a0from the idle screen.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.13.9-InternationalCurrencySupport\">International Currency Support</h3><p>International currency support has arrived\u00a0in Qpop. Now the currency configured for your RepairQ will also apply to any Qpop companions you assign.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.13.9-Trade-inItemRemoval\">Trade-in\u00a0Item Removal</h2><p>We now prevent removing a trade-in item once saved\u00a0to prevent any unexpected changes to inventory or attached refurb tickets. Once inventory is received via a tradein ticket,\u00a0reversing the transaction should now be performed via voiding the ticket. You can still remove a pending trade-in item without any trouble.</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
